//string conceitos Gene Genotype Phenotype Heterozygote Homozygous Dominant Recessive Codominance Allele Gametes Dihybridisme Monohybridisme You are in the concept screen to navigate through them just swipe up or down, to return to the menu, make an reverse L anywhere on the screen Gene, Are specific sequences of nucleotides in DNA that constitute the fundamental unit of heredity. Genotype, Group of genes of the individual. Phenotype, Group of physical and physiological characteristics of an individual that results of the expression of the model and action of the environment. Heterozygote, When an individual has two different alleles of the same gene Homozygous, When an individual has two equal alleles of the same gene Dominant, The allele is expressed in a homozygous condition and in a heterozygous condition Recessive, The allele is only expressed in homozygosis for that reason it has no phenotypic effect when in heterozygosis Codominance, Situation in which the expression of the phenotypes of both alleles is observed when presented in heterozygosis Allele, alternative form of a gene that affects the same characteristic differently. Gametes, are cells involved in sexual reproduction Heredity: transmission of resources from parents to their descendants. Dihybridisme, this term refers to Mendel\'s second law, where differences in one characteristic are inherited regardless of differences in another characteristic. Monohybridisme, this term refers to Mendel\'s first law, and applies to hybrid individuals, considering only one characteristic. REVIEW CONCEPTS
